    <div> Patient Consent and Notification Background:</div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="requlartext">
    <div>Hypertension (also known as high blood pressure) and diabetes (also known as high blood
    sugar) are growing health concerns in Sub-Saharan Africa and across the world. You are being invited to
    participate in the Medtronic Labs SPICE™ Management program because you have hypertension or
    diabetes or both. </div>
    <div> Managing your condition, attending clinic appointments, getting prescriptions filled,
    and being compliant with your medications and management plan can be challenging. It can also be difficult
    for
    your health care provider, such as your doctor, to track your blood pressure (BP) or blood glucose, health
    status, and medication information over time.</div>
    <div> The Medtronic Labs SPICE™ program, uses a new
    method to improve clinical care for patients with hypertension and diabetes. This program seeks to track
    your BP
    and blood glucose data over time and to present it in an understandable way for your health care provider,
    empower you by providing more information about your hypertension and diabetes status, with the overall
    goals of
    providing improved care to reduce related complications and challenges.</div>
    <div>Program Procedures</div>
    <div>As a participant in this program, you will:
    <ul>
        <li> Be requested to visit the clinic/ hospital for enrollment
        into the program. You will be informed about the program and if you agree to participate, will be
        enrolled
        into
        the Medtronic Labs SPICE™ system.</li>
        <li>Receive educational information about
        hypertension and diabetes.</li>
        <li>Be asked to comply with the follow-up plan your health care provider
        provides you to the best of your ability:</li>
        <li>Regularly have your BP and blood glucose checked , per
        your follow-up plan.</li>
        <li>Attend hospital/ clinic medical reviews to see your health care provider, per
        your follow-up plan.</li>
        <li>Receive and review short message service (SMS) messages with information from
        your health care provider.</li>
    </ul>
    </div>
    <div>Risk(s):
    <div> Risks associated with this program include delays or inaccurate
        information getting to your doctor or nurse that might potentially impact your care. To minimize this
        risk,
        we
        are using automated BP monitors and glucometers that are already approved to be purchased locally. All
        software
        being used has been carefully tested to make sure it is functioning as expected and is accurate. There
        are
        also
        checks in the system to ensure your information is being sent to your doctor.<div>In situations where
        you
        are
        instructed to go to the hospital/ clinic your doctor or nurse will be notified via SMS and will
        follow-up
        with
        you. In this regard, you are required to provide accurate contact information (i.e. telephone
        number) to
        your
        doctor and you will be required to inform your doctor in the event of any change of such contact
        information.</div>
    </div>
    </div>
    <div>Benefit(s):
    <div>Patient and population benefits:</div>
    <ul>
        <li>You may learn more about your
        condition and how to better your health status.</li>
        <li>You will have access to regular BP and blood
        glucose measurements and will receive clear actionable information, which may help you in managing your
        hypertension and/ or diabetes.</li>
        <li>Information collected from the program may be used to further
        benefit future similar patients or family members with hypertension, diabetes or heart disease</li>
    </ul>
    </div>
    <div>Confidentiality/ Use of Personal Information:
    <div>While participating in this program the following
        information will be collected:
        <ul>
        <li>Identifying information (age, gender, phone number) and medical data
            and health information from you and from your medical records as prepared by your doctor including
            treatment
            and
            examination notes, and other health related information</li>
        <li>You will be assigned a program ID that will be
            used for unique identification and to protect data privacy.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div>Your doctor, nurse, pharmacist, those checking
        your BP or blood glucose, and other designated parties that are involved in the program (for example
        those
        processing the program data) may have direct access to your personal information.</div>
    <div>As an enrolled
        participant in the program, your personal information will be transferred to the United States as part
        of
        processing, with computing support from the software team in India. The program team will have your
        personal
        SPICE information processed manually or by computer, including the use of internet or of cloud computing. By
        enrolling
        in the program, you agree to the said transfer, storage and processing of your personal information.
        Data
        results from the program may be published but will not disclose your name or any other identifying
        characteristics. No personal information will be used to market to you without your consent.</div>
    <div>Your
        de-identified medical information may also be used for additional research, educational purposes,
        publications,
        population health review, future health studies, development of new medical products or procedures, or
        for
        obtaining future approvals for health systems. In addition, the program team may also be required to
        disclose
        your personal information and health information if required by law or by a court order.</div>
    <div>There is no
        patient portal to access your personal information collected as part of this program, but this
        information
        can
        be requested directly from your doctor or nurse.</div>
    <div>The program will handle your personal information in
        accordance with appropriate confidentiality standards and all applicable data protection and privacy
        laws.
    </div>
    </div>
    <div>Participation:
    <div>Whether you take part in this program is up to you. If you choose to join the program, you
        may stop at any time, and this will not affect your current medical care.</div>
    <div>Please notify your doctor or
        nurse if you would like to withdraw.</div>
    <div>You may also choose not to answer any question you find uncomfortable
        or private during the program. There will be no consequence, loss of benefit or care to you if you
        choose to
        leave the program. Your collected data may be used as part of the program, unless you request otherwise.
    </div>
    <div>Program team members from may reach out to you via SMS or calls to ask about your experience or in
        follow-up to
        missed assessment or medical reviews, as part of tele-counseling services. You may notify them if you
        wish
        to
        not receive any calls or SMS.</div>
    </div>
    <div>Compensation:
    <div>You will not receive any compensation for participating
        in this program.</div>
    </div>
    <div>SMS:
    <div>By signing up for the program, you are accepting to receive SMS messages used
        for communication of messages from your doctor or nurse, or instructions to pick up filled
        prescriptions.
        SMS
        messages from the software application will not be used for marketing purposes. If you wish to stop
        receiving
        the SMS messages, kindly inform your doctor or nurse.</div>
    </div>
    <div>Secondary use of data:
    <div> Your de-identified
        medical information may be combined with data from other program participants and used by the program
        team
        for
        research, marketing, or publication purposes, or to inform on the performance of the Medtronic Labs
        SPICE™ system.</div>
    </div>
    <div>Additionally, your de-identified medical information along with other
    patients’ may also be used by program stakeholders, such as the Ministry of Health and County/Regional
    Health teams, as part of their assessment of overall patient population health and to evaluate trends.</div>
    <div>Identifying information will be removed from individual patient records before sharing with program
    stakeholders
    to protect patient privacy.</div>
    <div>Consent for the secondary uses of program data is separate from your medical
    treatment and does not affect your care.</div>
    <div>Contacts:
    <div>If you have any questions concerning this
        program, please do not hesitate to contact your doctor or nurse or
        <a href="mailto:support@medtroniclabs.org">support@medtroniclabs.org</a>
    </div>
    </div>
