    ('<!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head> <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" /> <style> html, body { max-width: 100%; overflow-x: hidden; } .requlartext { font-size: 16px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6; } .boldtext { font-size: 16px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.6; } /* Extra small devices (phones, 600px and down) */ @media only screen and (max-width: 600px) { .requlartext { font-size: 16px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6; } .boldtext { font-size: 16px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.6; } } /* Small devices (portrait tablets and large phones, 600px and up) */ @media only screen and (min-width: 600px) { .requlartext { font-size: 20px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6; } .boldtext { font-size: 20px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.6; } } /* Medium devices (landscape tablets, 768px and up) */ @media only screen and (min-width: 768px) { .requlartext { font-size: 20px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6; } .boldtext { font-size: 20px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.6; } } /* Large devices (laptops/desktops, 992px and up) */ @media only screen and (min-width: 992px) { .requlartext { font-size: 20px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6; } .boldtext { font-size: 20px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.6; } } /* Extra large devices (large laptops and desktops, 1200px and up) */ @media only screen and (min-width: 1200px) { .requlartext { font-size: 20px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6; } .boldtext { font-size: 20px; font-family: \"Inter\"; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.6; } } </style> </head> <body> <p class=\"boldtext\"> <b> Medtronic Labs Empower Health&trade;<br /> Patient Consent and Notification<br /> Background:<br /> </b> </p> <p class=\"requlartext\"> Hypertension (also known as high blood pressure) and diabetes (also known as high blood sugar) are growing health concerns in Sub-Saharan Africa and across the world. You are being invited to participate in the Medtronic Labs Empower Health&trade; Management program because you have hypertension or diabetes or both.<br /> Managing your condition, attending clinic appointments, getting prescriptions filled, and being compliant with your medications and management plan can be challenging. It can also be difficult for your health care provider, such as your doctor, to track your blood pressure (BP) or blood glucose, health status, and medication information over time.<br /> The Medtronic Labs Empower Health&trade; program, uses a new method to improve clinical care for patients with hypertension and diabetes. This program seeks to track your BP and blood glucose data over time and to present it in an understandable way for your health care provider, empower you by providing more information about your hypertension and diabetes status, with the overall goals of providing improved care to reduce related complications and challenges.<br /> Program Procedures<br /> As a participant in this program, you will:<br /> &bull; Be requested to visit the clinic/ hospital for enrollment into the program. You will be informed about the program and if you agree to participate, will be enrolled into the Medtronic Labs Empower Health&trade; system. <br /> &bull; Receive educational information about hypertension and diabetes.<br /> &bull; Be asked to comply with the follow-up plan your health care provider provides you to the best of your ability:<br /> &bull; Regularly have your BP and blood glucose checked , per your follow-up plan.<br /> &bull; Attend hospital/ clinic medical reviews to see your health care provider, per your follow-up plan.<br /> &bull; Receive and review short message service (SMS) messages with information from your health care provider.<br /> Risk(s):<br /> Risks associated with this program include delays or inaccurate information getting to your doctor or nurse that might potentially impact your care. To minimize this risk, we are using automated BP monitors and glucometers that are already approved to be purchased locally. All software being used has been carefully tested to make sure it is functioning as expected and is accurate. There are also checks in the system to ensure your information is being sent to your doctor.<br /> In situations where you are instructed to go to the hospital/ clinic your doctor or nurse will be notified via SMS and will follow-up with you. In this regard, you are required to provide accurate contact information (i.e. telephone number) to your doctor and you will be required to inform your doctor in the event of any change of such contact information.<br /> Benefit(s):<br /> Patient and population benefits:<br /> &bull; You may learn more about your condition and how to better your health status.<br /> &bull; You will have access to regular BP and blood glucose measurements and will receive clear actionable information, which may help you in managing your hypertension and/ or diabetes.<br /> &bull; Information collected from the program may be used to further benefit future similar patients or family members with hypertension, diabetes or heart disease<br /> Confidentiality/ Use of Personal Information:<br /> While participating in this program the following information will be collected:<br /> &bull; identifying information (age, gender, phone number) and medical data and health information from you and from your medical records as prepared by your doctor including treatment and examination notes, and other health related information<br /> You will be assigned a program ID that will be used for unique identification and to protect data privacy.<br /> Your doctor, nurse, pharmacist, those checking your BP or blood glucose, and other designated parties that are involved in the program (for example those processing the program data) may have direct access to your personal information.<br /> As an enrolled participant in the program, your personal information will be transferred to the United States as part of processing, with computing support from the software team in India. The program team will have your personal information processed manually or by computer, including the use of internet or of cloud computing. By enrolling in the program, you agree to the said transfer, storage and processing of your personal information. Data results from the program may be published but will not disclose your name or any other identifying characteristics. No personal information will be used to market to you without your consent.<br /> Your de-identified medical information may also be used for additional research, educational purposes, publications, population health review, future health studies, development of new medical products or procedures, or for obtaining future approvals for health systems. In addition, the program team may also be required to disclose your personal information and health information if required by law or by a court order.<br /> There is no patient portal to access your personal information collected as part of this program, but this information can be requested directly from your doctor or nurse.<br /> The program will handle your personal information in accordance with appropriate confidentiality standards and all applicable data protection and privacy laws.<br /> Participation<br /> Whether you take part in this program is up to you. If you choose to join the program, you may stop at any time, and this will not affect your current medical care.<br /> Please notify your doctor or nurse if you would like to withdraw.<br /> You may also choose not to answer any question you find uncomfortable or private during the program. There will be no consequence, loss of benefit or care to you if you choose to leave the program. Your collected data may be used as part of the program, unless you request otherwise.<br /> Program team members from may reach out to you via SMS or calls to ask about your experience or in follow-up to missed assessment or medical reviews, as part of tele-counseling services. You may notify them if you wish to not receive any calls or SMS.<br /> Compensation<br /> You will not receive any compensation for participating in this program.<br /> SMS<br /> By signing up for the program, you are accepting to receive SMS messages used for communication of messages from your doctor or nurse, or instructions to pick up filled prescriptions. SMS messages from the software application will not be used for marketing purposes. If you wish to stop receiving the SMS messages, kindly inform your doctor or nurse.<br /> Secondary use of data:<br /> Your de-identified medical information may be combined with data from other program participants and used by the program team for research, marketing, or publication purposes, or to inform on the performance of the Medtronic Labs Empower Health&trade; system.<br /> Additionally, your de-identified medical information along with other patients&rsquo; may also be used by program stakeholders, such as the Ministry of Health and County/Regional Health teams, as part of their assessment of overall patient population health and to evaluate trends.<br /> Identifying information will be removed from individual patient records before sharing with program stakeholders to protect patient privacy.<br /> Consent for the secondary uses of program data is separate from your medical treatment and does not affect your care.<br /> Contacts:<br /> If you have any questions concerning this program, please do not hesitate to contact your doctor or nurse or rs.mlempowerhealthclientcare@medtronic.com<br /> Statement of the person giving consent:<br /> I have read the information on this program or have had it translated into a language I understand. I have also talked it over to my satisfaction.<br /> I understand that my participation is voluntary.<br /> I know enough about the purpose, methods, risks, and benefits of the program to decide that I want to take part in it.<br /> I understand that I may freely stop being part of this program at any time without having to explain myself.<br /> I understand and agree that, as part of the program, the program team shall collect my personal information which may be disclosed to doctors, nurses, pharmacists, and BP/Glucose checkers, and other parties that are involved in the program as well as other third parties.<br /> I understand that the program may be modified, amended, or terminated at any time with or without notice.<br /> I understand and agree that the program team will store my personal information for a period of up to ten (10) years after the conclusion of the program.<br /> If requested, I have received a copy of this consent and notification form to keep for myself.<br /> The Healthcare worker will be accepting the above-mentioned Terms and Conditions on behalf of Screening Participant<br /> </p> </body> </html>','Assessment','Consent_form',false,1,1,1,1,false,true,1),
